https://codeforces.com/problemset/problem/263/A

In this problem we just have to find the position of 1 in the matrix then we are done
then the number of steps to move to the  center would be horizontal + vertical 
there is no other way just you have to go straight toward the center 
so 

#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    int i,j,a;
    for(i=0;i<5;++i)
    for(j=0;j<5;++j){
        cin>>a; 
        if(a==1)cout<<(abs(2-i)+abs(2-j));
        
    }
    
}

in js we can do simply 
 
for(var i=0;i<5;i++){
	var j=readline().split(' ').indexOf('1');
	if(j>-1){
		break;
	}
}
print( Math.abs(2-i)+Math.abs(2-j) );
